    public class Event<T extends HasMetadata>
extends AbstractEvent<T>
    An AbstractEvent that represents another event that has occurred to a Kubernetes resource, usually as found in an EventCache implementation.

    Laird Nelson

        public Event(Object source,
             AbstractEvent.Type type,
             T priorResource,

        Creates a new Event.
        Parameters:
        source - the creator; must not be null
        type - the Type of this Event; must not be null
        priorResource - a HasMetadata representing the prior state of the Kubernetes resource this Event primarily concerns; may be—and often is—null
        resource - a HasMetadata representing a Kubernetes resource; must not be null
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if source, type or resource is null
